 1005
Your Honor,

I, Lauren Dixon, stand before you today to plead guilty to the offense of TV licence payment evasion. I want to emphasize that my actions were not intentional, as I genuinely believed that the bill had been paid. Regrettably, I had unknowingly been using the TV without a license for a period of 8 months. However, upon realizing my mistake, I promptly rectified the situation by obtaining a proper TV license.

I must also bring to your attention that I have no previous criminal record. This incident is an isolated occurrence and does not reflect my character or my usual law-abiding nature. It is essential to note that my willingness to admit my guilt demonstrates my integrity and my commitment to taking responsibility for my actions.

I understand the significance of this offense and the importance of complying with the law. As a result, I am prepared to make every effort necessary to rectify the situation. I am more than willing to take any necessary steps to ensure that the harm done is compensated for. I am also committed to taking proactive measures to prevent any future offenses of a similar nature.

Your Honor, I wholeheartedly acknowledge the severity of my actions. However, I believe it is important to consider the context and circumstances surrounding my case. I assure you that there was no deliberate intent to evade payment, and my swift action to rectify the situation further demonstrates my remorse and commitment to making things right.

I stand before you today fully aware of the consequences I must face for my actions. However, I kindly request that you consider the mitigating factors present in my case. These include my clean criminal record, my immediate action to rectify the situation, and my genuine remorse for the offense committed.

In conclusion, I appreciate the opportunity to address the court and plead guilty to the charge of TV licence payment evasion. I assure you that I have learned my lesson and am committed to making amends. I respectfully request your leniency and understanding as we work towards a resolution that will allow me to rectify my mistake and continue on a positive path.

Thank you for your attention, Your Honor.
