NEW STATEMENT:

823
Your Honor,

I, Lauren Dixon, am here today to tender my guilty plea for the charge of TV license payment evasion. I want to emphasize that this plea is not only an expression of my remorse but also a recognition of my oversight in failing to settle the bill in a timely manner. 

It is crucial to underline that my failure to make the payment was not intentional. I genuinely believed that the bill had been paid, and I was unaware of the 8 months of unlicensed use. However, upon discovering my mistake, I immediately took action to rectify the situation by promptly obtaining a valid TV license.

In assessing my case, I would like to highlight that I have no previous criminal record. Prior to this incident, I have lived a law-abiding life, making this an isolated occurrence that does not represent my true character or reflect a pattern of behavior.

With deep regret, I accept full responsibility for my actions. My immediate effort to obtain a valid license, upon realizing my oversight, demonstrates my recognition of the mistake and my commitment to ensuring compliance in the future. I assure you that there was never any intention on my part to evade payment.

By offering my guilty plea, I wish to show the court that I am genuinely remorseful for my actions and that I understand the seriousness of the offense. I acknowledge that pleading guilty is a mitigating factor that benefits the court by saving time and resources that would otherwise be expended in a trial.

Your Honor, I humbly request your understanding and consideration of my candid expression of guilt, my clean criminal record, and my immediate efforts to rectify the situation as soon as I discovered my mistake. I sincerely hope that you will take these factors into account when determining an appropriate resolution to this matter.

Thank you, Your Honor, for your time and attention.
